      <scopecontent id="aspace_8e388f898346fedca220cd656fed03ab">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Mitchell Family Papers consist primarily of correspondence from Reverend John Mitchell to his wife, Mary Ann Tomlinson Mitchell. Correspondence of Sarah H. Tomlinson, Mary Ann's mother, as well as that of other family members, is included in the collection. The papers were the gift of Theodore Brooks in 1994.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_a783ed29835c8b90fb98d848db515d17">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>John Mitchell, 1794-1870</p>
         <p>John Mitchell graduated from Yale College in 1821. He was the editor of the <title render="italic">
               <part>Christian Spectator</part>
            </title>, a religious monthly published in New Haven from 1824-1829. In 1930 Mitchell was ordained as the first pastor of the First Congregational Church in Fair Haven and remained there until 1836. From 1836-1842 he was pastor of the Edward Congregational Church in Northampton. After resigning due to failing health, Mitchell travelled abroad and then settled in Stratford, Connecticut, where he became a writer. Among his publications is <title render="italic">
               <part>Scenes and Characters in College</part>
            </title>.</p>  
      </bioghist>
  
